# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Tutorial 14: chemical short-range order in a high-entropy alloy
#
# Render the final configurations of the three hybrid MD/MC runs at 1300 K
# (sro-hot.lmp, sro-2nnmeam.lmp, sro-sharifi.lmp) with the same view and
# colors as all figures of this tutorial:  Co = yellow (goldenrod),
# Cr = red (firebrick), Fe = blue (steelblue), Ni = green (seagreen).  A
# chromium precipitate shows up as a compact red ball, a partitioning into
# (Co,Fe)-rich and (Ni,Cr)-rich regions as separated yellow-blue and
# green-red domains, and a healthy solid solution as a uniform color mix.
# No forces are needed to render images, so pair_style zero is used.

variable cfg index hot 2nnmeam sharifi

label loop

clear
units metal
atom_style atomic
boundary p p p
pair_style zero 3.0
read_data ordered-${cfg}.data
pair_coeff * *

write_dump all image compare-${cfg}.png type type size 1024 1024 &
     zoom 1.2 view 60 30 box yes 0.02 shiny 0.2 ssao yes 4539 0.6 &
     modify backcolor white acolor 1 goldenrod acolor 2 firebrick &
     acolor 3 steelblue acolor 4 seagreen adiam 1 3.0 adiam 2 3.0 &
     adiam 3 3.0 adiam 4 2.5 boxcolor midnightblue element Co Cr Fe Ni

next cfg
jump SELF loop
